An example project showing how to use the vim-python-test-runner plugin with django

https://github.com/JarrodCTaylor/vim-python-test-runner

1.) mkvirtualenv example
2.) pip install -r requirements.txt
3.) install the plugin above (using Vundle or Pathogen)
4.) close and reopen vim from the project root
5.) :e website/tests/api_view_tests.py
6.) :DjangoTestFile

You can also test at the method level / class level

:DjangoTestClass
:DjangoTestMethod
